                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18410301-970-offence-1 t18410301-name-987"></join>George Christopher Hymns</persName>.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18410301-name-988" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18410301-name-988" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410301-name-988" type="surname" value="HYMNS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410301-name-988" type="given" value="ELIZABETH"></interp>ELIZABETH HYMNS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am the wife of George Christopher Hymns, and live in Long-alley, Moorfields—I go out nursing and charing. The pri<lb></lb>soner's sister lodged with me, and paid me 1<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. a week—the prisoner used to come to see her—on the 9th of February I went out, at seven o'clock in the morning, leaving the prisoner's sister in the room—as I was coming home, about eleven o'clock, I met the prisoner in Ball-alley—directly he saw me he threw down something in a bundle—the sleeve of my child's frock fell out, and I knew it—the prisoner ran away—I could not stop him—I gave him in charge afterwards—he said when taken that he did not wrap up the bundle—that was another bundle, which I found in the room, wrapped up in a flannel—he asked me to forgive him several times.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PAYNE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> I believe you found him in bed at his mother's? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes—he seemed very much <hi rend="italic">cut up</hi> about it, and cried.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18410301-name-989" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18410301-name-989" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410301-name-989" type="surname" value="KENCHETT"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410301-name-989" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM KENCHETT</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable G</hi> 26.) I accompanied the pro<lb></lb>secutrix to the prisoner's mother's—he begged for forgiveness several times—while I stood out on the landing, I heard the prisoner's sister in the room, chastising him, because he did not take the key to the prosecutrix, as she had directed him.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> Did you ask him, as you took him to the station, who tied up the bundle which you found in the room? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> I did.</p>
